19-6202. DISCLOSURE OF RESIDENTIAL STREET ADDRESS AND TELEPHONE NUMBER PROHIBITED — EXCEPTIONS. Notwithstanding any other provision of state law, a public agency shall not disclose to any person or entity the Idaho residential street address and telephone number of a judicial officer and such officer’s residing household members upon submission of an application and fee consistent with the provisions of section 19-6203, Idaho Code, except under any of the following circumstances:

(1) If directed by a court order, to a person identified in the court order;

(2) If requested by a law enforcement agency, to the law enforcement agency;

(3) If requested by a financial institution or title company for business purposes, to the requesting financial institution or title company; or

(4) If the judicial officer provides written permission for disclosure of such information.

[(19-6202) 19-6002, added 2023, ch. 179, sec. 1, p. 483; am. and redesig. 2024, ch. 16, sec. 5, p. 138.]
